 z(t)=1+e^{it} 
 \begin{align} \frac1{z(t)} &=\frac1{1+e^{it}}\\ &=\frac1{1+\cos(t)+i\sin(t)}\frac{1+\cos(t)-i\sin(t)}{1+\cos(t)-i\sin(t)}\\[6pt] &=\frac{1+\cos(t)-i\sin(t)}{(1+\cos(t))^2+\sin^2(t)}\\[6pt] &=\frac{1+\cos(t)-i\sin(t)}{2+2\cos(t)}\\[6pt] &=\frac12-\frac i2\tan\left(\frac t2\right) \end{align} 
